description: After so many requests for post earrings like my dangle plugs I whipped up these. They feature a flower and a matching bead that accents a great printed guitar pick. The posts are silver filled. I also made pairs with kidney wires so if you have stretched ears you can wear them through a pair of tunnels. The kidney wires are silver plated and may contain nickel. 1/10 Silver-filled, which means that the outer 10% of each item is .925 silver over a brass core. Unlike silver plate, which can wear off quite quickly, silver filled will keep its beauty through years of daily wear. Just use the same precautions you would with real silver jewelry - don't expose to harsh chemicals, and when not in use, store in a dry, airtight bag or container.
